Problem Extreme/critical variation in drug efﬁcacy in spheroids treated with identical drug concentrations

Possible reason Irregular replacement of supernatant leading to different drug concentrations in parallel wells

Solution/action Be sure to replace (and to keep) 50% of the original supernatant in all wells, i.e., before the addition of 100 ml of new drug solution, the supernatant kept in each well should be 100 ml Check incubation conditions and incubator functions, i.e., water level Guarantee drug solubility and provide appropriate stock solutions Always start with the lowest drug concentration both when providing the drugs and when feeding the respective spheroids after treatment Use new tips for each concentration In general, perform all experiments according to good laboratory practice (GLP) conditions (or good manufacturing practice; GMP) and provide standard operating procedures Mix buffer/substrate solution immediately and exclusively before use and avoid light exposure

