ANTICIPATED RESULTS Our protocol provides some routine, easy-handling and reliable tools that allow a direct and rapid comparison of drug efﬁcacy in monolayer and spheroid culture. The initial analytical end point cell integrity as determined through the APH cell viability assay (Fig. 5) combined with the monitoring of spheroid integrity and volume growth (Fig. 6) is sufﬁcient to identify drug candidates that lose efﬁcacy in a 3D tissue structure Time PrePost and vice versa to approve those that scale target molecules or conditions developed in a 3D environment. The testing of Culture numerous drugs that are in clinical use is handling envisioned to unequivocally prove the 72 h clinical predictive signiﬁcance of the test treatment interval strategy as compared with less complex Days –12–11 ≥ 25 –8 9 11 13 4 –4 7 assay systems and in vivo models. 0 Spheroids can thus become a valid tool Phase contrast imaging Spheroid integrity and volume for negative and positive selection of the Analysis Time required APH assay most promising candidates in drug • to evaluate spheroid formation capacity Cell viability development programs resulting in • to monitor effect of drug on spheroid cell survival • to determine effect of drug on spheroid growth kinetics economical savings. We identiﬁed the APH assay as a Figure 4 | Time table for setting up and performing standardized spheroid-based drug tests with reliable and rapid handling tool for established tumor cell lines using cell survival after treatment (APH assay) and growth delay (spheroid monitoring cell viability in single volume growth and regrowth, respectively) as analytical end points.
